  "prompt": "When will we lose muscle mass in our body?",
  "response": "Muscle mass typically begins to decline as we age, a process known as sarcopenia. Here are key points about muscle loss:\n\n1. Age-related muscle loss\n- Begins around age 30\n- Accelerates after age 40\n- More significant after age 50-60\n\n2. Factors contributing to muscle loss\n- Decreased hormone levels\n- Reduced physical activity\n- Poor nutrition\n- Decreased protein intake\n- Chronic diseases\n- Sedentary lifestyle\n\n3. Rate of muscle loss\n- About 3-5% muscle mass lost per decade after age 30\n- Can increase to 8% per decade after age 60\n\n4. Prevention strategies\n- Regular resistance/strength training\n- Adequate protein intake\n- Balanced diet\n- Regular exercise\n- Maintaining hormonal balance\n- Staying physically active\n\n5. Additional circumstances causing muscle loss\n- Prolonged bed rest\n- Injury\n- Certain medical conditions\n- Malnutrition\n- Lack of physical activity\n\nMaintaining an active lifestyle and proper nutrition can significantly slow down muscle loss and help preserve muscle mass as you age.",
